{"article_id":"MKUg6knEhuG1XTCX","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON/SEOUL","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"( ) -","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"U.S. President Donald Trump late on Friday said","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"the United States was having \" productive talks \"","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"about reinstating a June 12 summit with North Korea ' s leader Kim Jong Un ,","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"just a day after he canceled the meeting","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"citing Pyongyang ' s \" open hostility . \"","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"\" We are having very productive talks","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"about reinstating the Summit","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"which ,","depth":13},{"id":10,"text":"if it does happen ,","depth":14},{"id":11,"text":"will likely remain in Singapore on the same date , June 12th. ,","depth":14},{"id":12,"text":"and ,","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"if necessary ,","depth":14},{"id":14,"text":"will be extended beyond that date , \"","depth":14},{"id":15,"text":"Trump said in a Twitter post .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"South Korea ' s presidential spokesman said in response :","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"\" We are cautiously optimistic","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"that hope is still alive for US-North Korea dialogue .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"We are continuing to watch developments carefully . \"","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Trump had earlier indicated","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"the summit could be salvaged","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"after welcoming a conciliatory statement from North Korea","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"saying","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"it remained open to talks .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"\" It was a very nice statement","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"they put out , \"","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"Trump told reporters at the White House .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"\" We ' ll see what happens -","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"it could even be the 12th . \"","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"We ' re talking to them now .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"They very much want to do it .","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"We ' d like to do it . \"","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"After years of tension over Pyongyang ' s nuclear weapons program , Kim and Trump agreed this month to hold what would be the first meeting between a serving U.S. president and a North Korean leader .","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"The plan followed months of war threats and insults between the leaders over North Korea ' s development of missiles","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"capable of reaching the United States .","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"Trump scrapped the meeting ,","depth":15},{"id":37,"text":"planned for Singapore ,","depth":15},{"id":38,"text":"in a letter to Kim on Thursday","depth":14},{"id":39,"text":"after repeated threats by North Korea to pull out over what it saw as confrontational remarks by U.S. officials","depth":14},{"id":40,"text":"demanding unilateral disarmament .","depth":14},{"id":41,"text":"Trump cited North Korean hostility","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"in canceling the summit .","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"In Pyongyang , North Korean Vice Foreign Minister Kim Kye Gwan said","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"North Korea ' s criticisms had been a reaction to American rhetoric","depth":14},{"id":45,"text":"and that current antagonism showed \" the urgent necessity \" for the summit .","depth":14},{"id":46,"text":"He said","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"North Korea regretted Trump ' s decision","depth":15},{"id":48,"text":"to cancel","depth":15},{"id":49,"text":"and remained open to resolving issues","depth":15},{"id":50,"text":"\" regardless of ways , at any time . \"","depth":15},{"id":51,"text":"Kim Kye Gwan said","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"North Korea had appreciated Trump","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"having made the bold decision","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"to work toward a summit .","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"\" We even inwardly hoped","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"that what is called ' Trump formula ' would help clear both sides of their worries","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"and comply with the requirements of our side","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"and would be a wise way of substantial effect","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"for settling the issue , \"","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"Trump ' s latest about-face sent officials scrambling in Washington .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"Defense Secretary Jim Mattis told reporters","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"diplomats were \" still at work \"","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"and said","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"Trump had just sent a note out on the summit ,","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"which could be back on","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"\" if our diplomats can pull it off . \"","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"U.S. State Department spokeswoman Katina Adams declined to give details of any diplomatic contacts","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"but said :","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"\" As the president said in his letter to Chairman Kim ,","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"dialogue between the two is the only dialogue","depth":16},{"id":72,"text":"that matters .","depth":16},{"id":73,"text":"If North Korea is serious ,","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"then we look forward hearing from them at the highest levels . \"","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"White House spokeswoman Sarah Sanders told reporters","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"Trump did not want a meeting","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"that was \" just a political stunt . \"","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"U.S. President Donald Trump leaves the White House for a trip to Annapolis , Maryland , in Washington , U.S.","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"May 25 , 2018 .","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"/Carlos Barria","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"\" He wants to get something","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"that ' s a long-lasting and an actual real solution .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"And","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"if they are","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"they are ready to do that","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"then ...","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"we ' re certainly ready to have those conversations , \"","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"she said .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"North Korea had sharply criticized suggestions by Trump ' s national security adviser , John Bolton , and Vice President Mike Pence","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"that it could share the fate of Libya","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"if it did not swiftly surrender its nuclear arsenal .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi was deposed and killed by NATO-backed militants","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"after halting his nascent nuclear program .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Trump had initially sought to placate North Korea ,","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"he was not pursuing the \" Libya model \"","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"and Sanders said","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"he was following \" the President Trump model . \"","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"U.S. regional allies Japan and South Korea , as well as North Korea ' s main ally , China , urged the two countries to salvage the summit on Friday .","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"At an economic forum in St. Petersburg , Chinese Vice President Wang Qishan said","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"it was necessary to ensure security on the Korean peninsula ,","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"which touched on China ' s core interests .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe , at the same forum , regretted the cancellation","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"and said","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"the world should keep doing its bit","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"to make the summit happen .","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"South Korea also would continue efforts","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"to improve ties with the North ,","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"the office of President Moon Jae-in said","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"after Moon ' s top security advisers met for the second time on Friday .","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"Some analysts worried","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"that canceling the summit could prompt a resumption in hostilities ,","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"including renewed shorter-range missile tests or stepped-up cyber attacks by Pyongyang and increased sanctions or deployment of new military assets by Washington .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"In his letter , Trump warned Kim of the United States ' greater nuclear might ,","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"reminiscent of his tweet last year","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"asserting","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"that he had a \" much bigger \" nuclear button than Kim .","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"While the Trump administration had insisted on North Korea ' s complete , verifiable and irreversible dismantling of its nuclear program ,","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"Pyongyang had always couched its language in terms of denuclearisation of the Korean peninsula .","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"It has said in previous , failed talks","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"that it could consider giving up its arsenal","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"if the United States provided security guarantees","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"by removing its troops from South Korea","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"and withdrawing its so-called nuclear umbrella of deterrence from South Korea and Japan .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":249,"left":0,"right":248,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":248,"left":1,"right":247,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":247,"left":221,"right":246,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":221,"left":203,"right":220,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":200,"right":202,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":142,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":138,"right":141,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent